the aws-auth ConfigMap. This reduces the risk of manual errors and misconfigurations. 2. Enhanced Auditing and Compliance: The API offers better visibility into cluster access configurations, facilitating easier auditing and compliance checks. Administrators can list and describe access entries and policies directly through the EKS API. 3. Improved Operational Efficiency: The API streamlines access management, reducing operational overhead and minimizing the risk of misconfigurations. 4. Simplified Policy Management: The Cluster Access Manager API provides a more streamlined approach to managing access policies, making them easier to create, update, and manage.

